INSTALL 

2.1  System Requirements

To ensure Anteater Chess program will run correctly on your device, the following requirements must be met:
	
	- Operating System: Windows, macOS Ventura or later, or Linux
	- Processor: Intel I3 or equivalent (minimum)
	- Memory: 4 GB minimum
	- Storage: At least 200 MB of free disk space
	- Others: GCC Compiler
	- Internet: For updates (optional)

2.2  Setup and Configuration

Please refer to these instructions when installing Anteater Chess:

Step 1: Download Program

	Obtain source code
		- Can be done through Canvas submission files

Step 2: Extract Files 
	
	If the program file is compressed, extract it using the following:
		- gtar xvzf Chess_Alpha_src.tar.gz
		cd anteater_chess

Step 3: Compile the Program
	
	Use the following makefile to generate executable file “AnteaterChess”: 
		make 

Step 4: Run the Program

	Run the following line to start the program:
		./bin/chess

Step 5: Follow the Directions on Screen

	To start a game:
		1. Choose your difficulty level(Easy/Medium/Hard)
		2. Pick the side you wanna play as(Black/White)
		3. Select if you want to play vs AI or Human
		4. Hit Enter to Start

